  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This work product describes how to configure a tool for enterprise-wide deployment.&amp;nbsp;Tool configurations are often&#xD;
    associated with method assets, because the tool may automate - or be configured to be consistent with - a given&#xD;
    process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Some examples of tool configurations include - but is not limited to - the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Preference settings&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Permissions&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Report definitions&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Descriptions of requirements attributes and traceability for a requirements management tool&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Project templates for a project management tool such as Rational(R) Team Concert.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this work product is to simplify usage of tools by standardizing on configurations that are proven to&#xD;
    work with the organization's processes.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>Each&amp;nbsp;team must learn how to configure tools on their own if&amp;nbsp;defined enterprise tool configurations&amp;nbsp;do not&#xD;
exist.&amp;nbsp;It would be difficult for teams to evaluate the effectiveness of tools&amp;nbsp;and make&amp;nbsp;improvements if such&#xD;
configurations do not exist.&amp;nbsp;</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>Smaller organizations may choose not to define standard tool configurations because there aren't enough teams to benefit&#xD;
from reuse.&amp;nbsp;If you have tools that are easy to configure correctly without the need for standard configurations to&#xD;
exist, then this artifact is not needed.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <representationOptions>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Representation options include a document that describes how to configure the tool, a report from a configured tool&#xD;
    that describes how the tool is configured, or the actual files used to configure the tool.&#xD;
&lt;/p></representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
